Key players


Indian’s page:
Same structure as Cav’s
The Cleveland Indians have been around since 1901. The have won two World Series since. The Cleveland team originated in 1900 as the Lake Shores, when the American League (AL) was officially a minor league. There mascot is a completely un-related being named Slider
News:

Amazing turn of events

On July 11th the Indians beat out the White Sox. It was an epic game, that some would say was decided by a replay. Asdrubal Cabrera was ruled safe at second after a manager’s challenge. In doing this, the Indians found themselves still on offense in the fifth inning. Lonnie Chisenhall had a huge hit that tied the game, and got himself on base.  Nick Swisher, then had a huge homerun that put the Indians up. The win breaks a four game losing streak to the White Sox, and puts the Indians at .500 for the first time since June 20th.


Brown’s page:
Same structure as Cav’s
The Browns have been around in the NFL since 1950. The Browns had early success in their existence. In 1995, the Browns were moved to Baltimore for a year, and for another three years, the Browns were without a football team. Since then, the team has been growing and developing.
News

Josh Gordon Arrested for DWI

Wide receiver Josh Gordon was arrested for DWI on July 5th in North Carolina. Gordon got pulled over at 3 a.m. for going 50mph in a 35mph zone.  His BAL (blood alcohol level) was 0.9 at the time of his arrest, just above North Carolina’s limit of 0.8. He admitted to drinking three vodka drinks. Gordon is to be in court on August 26. He is facing a one year suspension from the NFL. Last year, Josh Gordon was pulled over for speeding. Officers found pot in his Mercedes and a passenger was cited for possession of marijuana. Gordon was suspended for two games at the beginning of the 2013 season.

Quotes:

